1
00:00:43,210 --> 00:00:45,445
<i>I'm not safe in here.</i>

2
00:00:51,986 --> 00:00:54,656
<i>I feel like I'm being watched.</i>
<i>Like...</i>

3
00:00:57,959 --> 00:01:00,160
<i>...there's eyes on me.</i>

4
00:01:07,769 --> 00:01:09,771
I'm so scared.

5
00:02:43,296 --> 00:02:45,667
Mia!

6
00:02:57,779 --> 00:02:59,881
<i>The hosts of</i>
<i>the popular YouTube channel</i>

7
00:02:59,981 --> 00:03:03,017
<i>"Paranormal Paranoids" have now</i>
<i>been missing for a week.</i>

8
00:03:03,117 --> 00:03:05,185
<i>Speculation</i>
<i>abounds for the whereabouts</i>

9
00:03:05,285 --> 00:03:07,088
<i>of the so-called</i>
<i>"Paranormal Paranoids."</i>

10
00:03:07,187 --> 00:03:09,423
<i>Peter Bailey, Laura Tucker,</i>

11
00:03:09,524 --> 00:03:11,491
<i>David Reynolds,</i>
<i>and Riley Brennan.</i>

12
00:03:11,592 --> 00:03:13,226
<i>They were last</i>
<i>week near the southern edge</i>

13
00:03:13,326 --> 00:03:14,428
<i>of Darke County, Ohio,</i>

14
00:03:14,529 --> 00:03:17,364
<i>near an abandoned town</i>
<i>called Shelby Oaks.</i>

15
00:03:17,464 --> 00:03:18,733
<i>The Darke County</i>
<i>Police Department say</i>

16
00:03:18,833 --> 00:03:20,267
<i>they're doing their best</i>
<i>to locate them,</i>

17
00:03:20,367 --> 00:03:21,536
<i>but have very few leads.</i>

18
00:03:21,636 --> 00:03:23,270
<i>- These people are fakers, man.</i>

19
00:03:23,370 --> 00:03:24,739
They've always been frauds.

20
00:03:24,839 --> 00:03:25,740
<i>They're still frauds.</i>

21
00:03:25,840 --> 00:03:27,340
<i>- They're baiting you.</i>

22
00:03:27,441 --> 00:03:28,408
Just building anticipation
for the next episode.

23
00:03:28,509 --> 00:03:31,813
<i>- They recently started</i>
<i>using two cameras.</i>

24
00:03:31,913 --> 00:03:33,848
<i>The cops have one.</i>

25
00:03:33,948 --> 00:03:34,481
So, where's the other?

26
00:03:34,582 --> 00:03:36,316
<i>- The parents are requesting</i>

27
00:03:36,416 --> 00:03:38,418
<i>that the public take</i>
<i>this seriously.</i>

28
00:03:38,519 --> 00:03:39,654
<i>- This isn't a hoax.</i>

29
00:03:39,754 --> 00:03:41,889
<i>- It's been one full week</i>
<i>since we learned</i>

30
00:03:41,989 --> 00:03:42,824
<i>of their disappearance,</i>

31
00:03:42,924 --> 00:03:45,159
<i>without a new development</i>
<i>in the case,</i>

32
00:03:45,258 --> 00:03:47,195
<i>their friends and family</i>

33
00:03:47,294 --> 00:03:49,429
<i>are starting to fear</i>
<i>the worst.</i>

34
00:04:00,273 --> 00:04:02,442
This is Riley,
as you know her,

35
00:04:02,543 --> 00:04:05,378
host of "Paranormal Paranoids."

36
00:04:08,015 --> 00:04:12,520
This is Riley as I know her,
my little sister.

37
00:04:13,121 --> 00:04:15,322
My name is Mia Walker.

38
00:04:15,556 --> 00:04:18,492
I've been searching for Riley
for the last 12 years,

39
00:04:19,727 --> 00:04:23,330
and I'd like you to get to know
her the way that I do.

40
00:04:23,430 --> 00:04:29,302
♪ I'm haunted in the morning ♪

41
00:04:30,805 --> 00:04:33,875
One, two,
three, four...

42
00:04:33,975 --> 00:04:37,211
<i>When we were kids,</i>
<i>she was very mature for her age.</i>

43
00:04:37,310 --> 00:04:39,647
<i>She was always thinking,</i>

44
00:04:39,747 --> 00:04:42,617
<i>figuring things out,</i>
<i>seeing things no one else saw.</i>

45
00:04:42,717 --> 00:04:44,552
Some people keep
a dream journal.

46
00:04:44,652 --> 00:04:45,887
Riley kept a dream sketchbook.

47
00:04:45,987 --> 00:04:49,456
<i>She'd start drawing instantly,</i>
<i>as soon as she woke up.</i>

48
00:04:49,557 --> 00:04:51,225
<i>She had extremely vivid dreams.</i>

49
00:04:51,324 --> 00:04:54,195
<i>And sometimes...</i>

50
00:04:54,294 --> 00:04:57,532
she even drew her nightmares.

51
00:05:00,735 --> 00:05:02,469
♪ I wonder where I'm falling ♪

52
00:05:02,570 --> 00:05:03,671
<i>In high school,</i>

53
00:05:03,771 --> 00:05:05,907
<i>she started to take the arts</i>
<i>more seriously.</i>

54
00:05:06,007 --> 00:05:08,843
<i>And the Riley that</i>
<i>I knew just melted away</i>

55
00:05:08,943 --> 00:05:11,145
<i>when she was performing.</i>

56
00:05:11,245 --> 00:05:14,381
She really came out
of her shell.

57
00:05:14,481 --> 00:05:17,218
And she got good at that.

58
00:05:17,819 --> 00:05:20,621
<i>Pretending that she was okay</i>
<i>when she wasn't.</i>

59
00:05:21,923 --> 00:05:27,427
♪ Big sister,
won't you find me ♪

60
00:05:27,528 --> 00:05:28,996
<i>So, with that passion</i>
<i>of hers,</i>

61
00:05:29,096 --> 00:05:31,966
<i>it was no surprise</i>
<i>when the channel took off.</i>

62
00:05:34,735 --> 00:05:37,738
<i>For the last half</i>
<i>of the 20th century,</i>

63
00:05:37,839 --> 00:05:40,541
<i>UFO researchers,</i>
<i>demonologists, psychics,</i>

64
00:05:40,641 --> 00:05:43,343
<i>all that, there was</i>
<i>a mysticism to it.</i>

65
00:05:43,443 --> 00:05:45,980
<i>Even the idea of investigating</i>
<i>the supernatural</i>

66
00:05:46,080 --> 00:05:47,782
<i>was becoming a joke.</i>

67
00:05:49,083 --> 00:05:51,285
What happened with
the Paranoids changed that.

68
00:05:51,418 --> 00:05:54,255
- Since then, locals refer
to it simply as

69
00:05:54,354 --> 00:05:56,023
"The Suicide Shed".

70
00:05:56,123 --> 00:05:58,092
<i>YouTube was brand new.</i>

71
00:05:58,192 --> 00:06:00,360
<i>Nobody knew what it could be,</i>
<i>or who might be watching.</i>

72
00:06:00,460 --> 00:06:02,730
<i>The Paranoids tapped</i>
<i>into an audience</i>

73
00:06:02,830 --> 00:06:06,567
<i>that had been relegated</i>
<i>to UFO conventions,</i>

74
00:06:06,667 --> 00:06:08,536
and paranormal chatrooms,

75
00:06:08,636 --> 00:06:10,605
and those people were starved
for content.

76
00:06:10,705 --> 00:06:13,473
<i>Nearly every time</i>
<i>they filmed,</i>

77
00:06:13,574 --> 00:06:15,743
<i>they captured something</i>
<i>most paranormal researchers</i>

78
00:06:15,843 --> 00:06:17,678
<i>spend their entire lives</i>
<i>looking for,</i>

79
00:06:17,945 --> 00:06:20,548
<i>which is why they had</i>
<i>so many doubters.</i>

80
00:06:20,648 --> 00:06:23,117
<i>You know, at first,</i>

81
00:06:23,217 --> 00:06:24,986
<i>I thought they could have been</i>
<i>faking things, sure.</i>

82
00:06:25,086 --> 00:06:27,420
<i>I mean, I didn't know how</i>
<i>else to explain it.</i>

83
00:06:28,189 --> 00:06:32,793
<i>But I also knew that Riley</i>
<i>wouldn't do something like that.</i>

84
00:06:32,894 --> 00:06:35,696
<i>She took all this stuff</i>
<i>very seriously.</i>

85
00:06:37,497 --> 00:06:38,766
- What was that?

86
00:06:38,866 --> 00:06:42,203
Riley, don't go
all by yourself, Riley.

87
00:06:44,005 --> 00:06:45,239
Chill, chill.

88
00:06:45,339 --> 00:06:46,874
Where did
that come from?

89
00:06:50,244 --> 00:06:52,713
- Whoa! Whoa!
- Holy shit!

90
00:06:57,652 --> 00:07:00,487
- I believe
my sister's not a liar.

91
00:07:01,555 --> 00:07:03,758
<i>I tried talking to her about it</i>

92
00:07:03,858 --> 00:07:07,295
<i>but after the prison episode,</i>
<i>she got real quiet.</i>

93
00:07:18,172 --> 00:07:19,941
- Jesus.

94
00:07:20,041 --> 00:07:21,474
What?

95
00:07:23,711 --> 00:07:25,379
- Don't you feel that?

96
00:07:25,613 --> 00:07:27,715
No. Feel what?

97
00:07:28,448 --> 00:07:30,084
- Cold.

98
00:07:32,653 --> 00:07:35,356
- Holy shit.
- Oh, fuck!

99
00:07:35,656 --> 00:07:38,893
Riley.
- What? What?

100
00:07:38,993 --> 00:07:40,661
- No, it's fine.

101
00:07:40,761 --> 00:07:42,229
- Wait!
- No, Riley!

102
00:07:42,330 --> 00:07:43,998
- Riley!
- Riley, no!

103
00:07:44,098 --> 00:07:46,200
- We have to go now!

104
00:07:47,368 --> 00:07:50,037
<i>A lot of people called</i>
<i>bullshit on that.</i>

105
00:07:51,405 --> 00:07:54,575
<i>But then the uploads stopped</i>
<i>and the channel went dark.</i>

106
00:07:54,675 --> 00:07:56,510
Some of the fans were worried,

107
00:07:56,610 --> 00:07:59,246
but most seemed to think it
was a publicity stunt.

108
00:08:00,414 --> 00:08:03,117
<i>And then... everything changed.</i>

109
00:08:03,217 --> 00:08:06,320
- Today's top story, the hosts
of the YouTube channel,

110
00:08:06,420 --> 00:08:10,791
the "Paranormal Paranoids"
have been missing for five days.

111
00:08:11,225 --> 00:08:14,161
<i>People started taking it</i>
<i>seriously after that.</i>

112
00:08:15,296 --> 00:08:16,430
<i>It's sad to say,</i>

113
00:08:16,530 --> 00:08:19,300
<i>but that's really where</i>
<i>their fame began.</i>

114
00:08:19,400 --> 00:08:21,802
<i>After their disappearance,</i>

115
00:08:21,902 --> 00:08:23,371
<i>people all over the world</i>

116
00:08:23,471 --> 00:08:25,039
<i>started scouring through</i>
<i>their videos</i>

117
00:08:25,139 --> 00:08:26,140
<i>searching for answers.</i>

118
00:08:26,240 --> 00:08:28,075
<i>There are videos</i>
<i>of her on her channel</i>

119
00:08:28,175 --> 00:08:31,012
<i>talking to someone</i>
<i>offscreen that we've never met.</i>

120
00:08:31,112 --> 00:08:32,446
<i>The police need to be</i>
<i>checking everything.</i>

121
00:08:32,546 --> 00:08:34,982
<i>Having clear sight</i>
<i>of a car belonging to a member</i>

122
00:08:35,082 --> 00:08:37,151
<i>of the group may also be helpful</i>
<i>for us going forward,</i>

123
00:08:37,251 --> 00:08:38,953
<i>if we ever need to identify</i>
<i>a vehicle.</i>

124
00:08:39,053 --> 00:08:40,554
<i>There were plenty</i>
<i>of theories,</i>

125
00:08:40,654 --> 00:08:42,056
<i>but nothing concrete</i>
<i>ever came forward.</i>

126
00:08:42,156 --> 00:08:44,625
<i>- So, there is a lot</i>
<i>to unpack here.</i>

127
00:08:44,725 --> 00:08:46,093
<i>- And then,</i>
<i>there's this odd clip</i>

128
00:08:46,193 --> 00:08:49,163
of her talking to another
Paranormal Paranoid, Peter.

129
00:08:59,006 --> 00:09:01,675
- Well, we had the gas station
security feed,

130
00:09:01,776 --> 00:09:03,110
and their card numbers.

131
00:09:03,210 --> 00:09:06,013
<i>They had made their last</i>
<i>recorded purchase</i>

132
00:09:06,113 --> 00:09:08,015
<i>there just outside</i>
<i>of Shelby Oaks.</i>

133
00:09:08,115 --> 00:09:12,086
<i>So, we knew they at least</i>
<i>got that far.</i>

134
00:09:12,186 --> 00:09:14,321
Anywhere they kids might
have been going,

135
00:09:14,422 --> 00:09:15,723
we had to investigate.

136
00:09:15,823 --> 00:09:19,160
<i>So, the most obvious place</i>
<i>was the old amusement park.</i>

137
00:09:21,562 --> 00:09:24,298
<i>It's about</i>
<i>60 miles from here.</i>

138
00:09:24,865 --> 00:09:26,867
<i>My mom used to talk about</i>
<i>it all the time.</i>

139
00:09:26,967 --> 00:09:28,669
<i>She loved going there</i>
<i>when she was a kid.</i>

140
00:09:29,804 --> 00:09:32,373
<i>They had a ballroom and</i>
<i>bands played there.</i>

141
00:09:32,473 --> 00:09:35,109
<i>It was pretty much the reason</i>
<i>to go to Shelby Oaks.</i>

142
00:09:36,677 --> 00:09:38,112
<i>The park closed</i>
<i>in the late 90s</i>

143
00:09:38,212 --> 00:09:41,615
<i>after a really bad fire.</i>

144
00:09:41,715 --> 00:09:44,685
<i>A lot of people think</i>
<i>the place is haunted.</i>

145
00:09:46,320 --> 00:09:51,992
<i>Shelby Oaks has been</i>
<i>a ghost town since the late 90s.</i>

146
00:09:52,093 --> 00:09:54,929
<i>From the perspective</i>
<i>of these kids, though,</i>

147
00:09:55,029 --> 00:09:58,432
<i>I mean, that place</i>
<i>was a gold mine.</i>

148
00:09:58,899 --> 00:10:04,772
<i>It seemed promising but</i>
<i>it was just another dead end.</i>

149
00:10:06,240 --> 00:10:08,008
- I know this is hard
for people to hear,

150
00:10:08,109 --> 00:10:11,812
but I don't think these are just
going to turn up anything.

151
00:10:11,912 --> 00:10:15,015
<i>I think the energy is better</i>
<i>spent on finding who did it.</i>

152
00:10:15,116 --> 00:10:18,018
<i>Every good cop</i>
<i>knows that feeling.</i>

153
00:10:18,520 --> 00:10:21,288
When it starts to sink in that
the person you're searching for

154
00:10:21,388 --> 00:10:23,357
isn't coming home.

155
00:10:25,192 --> 00:10:30,197
<i>Robert and I met two</i>
<i>years before Riley went missing.</i>

156
00:10:30,965 --> 00:10:32,833
I always wanted to be a mother

157
00:10:32,933 --> 00:10:35,236
and Robert always wanted
to be a daddy.

158
00:10:35,870 --> 00:10:40,908
And we tried for a bit but...
it didn't happen.

159
00:10:42,843 --> 00:10:44,845
<i>And then...</i>

160
00:10:44,945 --> 00:10:46,981
<i>when Riley went missing,</i>

161
00:10:47,081 --> 00:10:49,783
<i>it just...</i>

162
00:10:51,553 --> 00:10:54,321
...it just wasn't the time
anymore.

163
00:10:55,624 --> 00:10:56,891
<i>Not after that.</i>

164
00:11:57,918 --> 00:12:00,054
<i>Tragically,</i>
<i>the bodies of Peter Bailey,</i>

165
00:12:00,154 --> 00:12:02,022
<i>Laura Tucker,</i>
<i>and David Reynolds</i>

166
00:12:02,122 --> 00:12:05,259
<i>were found in a cabin just</i>
<i>outside of Shelby Oaks, Ohio,</i>

167
00:12:05,359 --> 00:12:07,228
<i>an abandoned ghost town</i>
<i>the young adults</i>

168
00:12:07,328 --> 00:12:09,631
<i>may have been investigating</i>
<i>for their show,</i>

169
00:12:09,730 --> 00:12:10,931
<i>"Paranormal Paranoids."</i>

170
00:12:11,031 --> 00:12:12,800
<i>On the front door</i>
<i>of the cabin,</i>

171
00:12:12,900 --> 00:12:16,003
<i>this disturbing symbol,</i>
<i>smeared in blood.</i>

172
00:12:16,103 --> 00:12:17,672
<i>Riley Brennan,</i>
<i>the host of the program,</i>

173
00:12:17,771 --> 00:12:19,473
<i>is still missing.</i>

174
00:12:19,574 --> 00:12:20,941
- I'm so scared.

175
00:12:21,041 --> 00:12:23,777
<i>A video camera</i>
<i>was discovered from the scene</i>

176
00:12:23,877 --> 00:12:27,147
<i>that police say may have</i>
<i>captured the perpetrator.</i>

177
00:12:38,158 --> 00:12:39,226
<i>Once the footage got out,</i>

178
00:12:39,326 --> 00:12:40,394
<i>it sparked a nationwide</i>
campaign.

179
00:12:40,494 --> 00:12:42,429
<i>I mean, you couldn't go</i>
<i>to the grocery store</i>

180
00:12:42,530 --> 00:12:44,965
<i>without seeing it</i>
<i>on a sign or a billboard.</i>

181
00:12:45,065 --> 00:12:47,835
- Who took Riley Brennan?

182
00:12:47,935 --> 00:12:50,170
<i>From the video,</i>
<i>we could ascertain</i>

183
00:12:50,271 --> 00:12:54,875
<i>that the suspect was</i>
<i>a white male, 6'1", maybe 6'2"</i>

184
00:12:54,975 --> 00:12:57,278
<i>based on the height</i>
<i>of the window.</i>

185
00:12:57,378 --> 00:12:59,113
<i>He was wearing gloves.</i>

186
00:12:59,213 --> 00:13:02,617
<i>So, basically we had nothing.</i>

187
00:13:02,717 --> 00:13:04,852
And...

188
00:13:05,620 --> 00:13:07,354
there was uh...

189
00:13:07,454 --> 00:13:09,456
there was that other thing.

190
00:13:12,893 --> 00:13:15,630
<i>We must've watched</i>
<i>that tape 500 times</i>

191
00:13:15,730 --> 00:13:18,299
<i>before releasing it</i>
<i>to the public.</i>

192
00:13:18,633 --> 00:13:20,401
<i>None of us saw it.</i>

193
00:13:21,368 --> 00:13:23,804
But now, like...

194
00:13:24,838 --> 00:13:27,074
can't get it outta my head.

195
00:13:38,919 --> 00:13:41,288
Oh, God.

196
00:13:51,733 --> 00:13:53,467
<i>Did I ever tell you</i>
<i>about the night terrors</i>

197
00:13:53,568 --> 00:13:54,868
<i>I used to have?</i>

198
00:13:55,836 --> 00:13:59,006
I'd see this man
in my window and...

199
00:14:00,441 --> 00:14:03,143
I just feel trapped.

200
00:14:03,243 --> 00:14:06,080
It's-it's, I mean,
it's weird, it's crazy.

201
00:14:06,180 --> 00:14:08,282
- No, no, you're fine.
- But like, I saw...

202
00:14:08,382 --> 00:14:11,218
like, images of...

203
00:14:12,219 --> 00:14:15,489
like, the school,
and the prison,

204
00:14:15,590 --> 00:14:18,158
and these numbers.
And--

205
00:14:18,258 --> 00:14:19,594
- Wait, after the fact,
or before?

206
00:14:19,694 --> 00:14:22,162
- No, like, when I was 13.

207
00:14:22,429 --> 00:14:24,031
<i>Riley always</i>
<i>had a connection.</i>

208
00:14:24,131 --> 00:14:25,099
<i>When she was little,</i>

209
00:14:25,199 --> 00:14:27,669
<i>she had these awful</i>
<i>night terrors.</i>

210
00:14:27,769 --> 00:14:29,203
<i>Like, we'd hear her screaming</i>

211
00:14:29,303 --> 00:14:31,539
<i>and Mom and I would run into</i>
<i>her room and find her sweating</i>

212
00:14:31,639 --> 00:14:33,575
<i>like she'd just run 10 miles.</i>

213
00:14:34,007 --> 00:14:36,210
<i>I'll never forget the way</i>
<i>her eyes looked.</i>

214
00:14:37,144 --> 00:14:39,079
<i>She kept saying</i>
<i>she saw a man</i>

215
00:14:39,179 --> 00:14:41,716
<i>standing in her window</i>
